name: eLifestyles
overview:
eCountryLifestyle is a slightly new concept in social networking. The term coined by the founders to describe this new concept is Virtual Lifestyle Community.

This concept wraps numerous lifestyle interests under a broad lifestyle term. The first Virtual Lifestyle Community is eCountryLifestyle which as it names implies specifically focus’ on country living interests and issues. The members (residents) have a say in the evolution of the site through the Townhall Meeting Forum.

To create a full community eCountryLifestyle includes clubs, trade associations, and other related organizations so that residents may fully learn, socialize, and more thoroughly enjoy the practice of their interests. Some of the many interests covered are; Gardening, Cooking, Home Improvement and Maintenance, Horses, Crafts, Candle making, Pottery making,Hunting, Fishing, Woodworking, Travel, Camping, Paddling, Cycling, Hiking, etc.

There are nine magazines with four or more new articles per week added to each magazine. There is also a video section, and of course profile pages, forums, chat rooms, and other interesting features including daily comics, crossword puzzles, jigsaw puzzles, and games.
